[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    41[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe risk profile is comparable to Recipes 3.6, 3.7, and 3.8 in clinical-safety consequence terms (the access-monitoring program contributes to HIPAA-breach-notification decisions and to HR employment actions; missed alerts produce undetected breaches that get reported late, which produces additional regulatory exposure; over-flagging produces wrongful-investigation labor exposure) but distinct in workforce-equity terms (the population being monitored is the workforce, which creates labor-relations and disparate-impact concerns that no other recipe in the chapter addresses), in regulatory-framework-breadth terms (HIPAA Security Rule audit controls, HIPAA Privacy Rule, HIPAA Breach Notification, ECPA, state-specific employee privacy statutes, NLRB protected concerted activity, collective bargaining), and in self-monitoring terms (the system contains highly sensitive workforce-and-patient data and must apply its own access-monitoring discipline to itself). The recipe correctly addresses the elevated risk in the Workforce-Notification-And-Acceptable-Use-Policy framing, the Equity-And-Subgroup-Performance-Audits-Are-Not-Optional framing, the Self-Monitoring-Of-The-Monitoring-System framing in Why This Isn't Production-Ready, and the Decommissioning-Criteria framing.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    42[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    43[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe Honest Take and the Why This Isn't Production-Ready section together are publication-ready voice; the "Healthcare has a specific structural problem" reframe and the Detection Pattern Catalog and the Identity, Patient, and Workforce Enrichment subsections are the recipe's biggest pedagogical contributions. The MEDIUM-finding cluster is an evenly distributed mix of architectural-completeness gaps (A1 idempotency, A2 DLQs, A3 privileged-user-separate-program, A4 service-account inventory, A5 new-user ramp-up cold-start, A6 care-relationship data-quality suppression workflow, A7 reference-data versioning) and PHI/governance backstops (S1 case payload PHI and workforce-PII minimization, S2 subgroup governance). These are the right next-pass priorities; with them addressed, Recipe 3.9 sits at the same publication-ready quality bar as Recipes 3.1-3.8.[K
