[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     51[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     52[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     53[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mBAA posture is explicit: "Signed AWS BAA. All services configured per BAA requirements. EHR vendor and any third-party patient-privacy-monitoring vendor must have their own BAAs" with a verified link to the [38;2;208;135;112m[[38;2;208;135;112mAWS HIPAA Eligible Services Reference[38;2;208;135;112m][38;2;208;135;112m([38;2;208;135;112mhttps://aws.amazon.com/compliance/hipaa-eligible-services-reference/[38;2;208;135;112m)[38;2;191;97;106m. The "EHR vendor and any third-party patient-privacy-monitoring vendor must have their own BAAs" framing is an important addition for a recipe that may integrate with commercial PPM products (Protenus, Imprivata FairWarning, MaizeAnalytics, Iatric); this is the discipline that distinguishes mature deployments from immature ones.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     54[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     55[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mEncryption coverage is complete across every PHI-and-PII-bearing store: "Customer-managed KMS keys on every PHI-bearing store: Kinesis, DynamoDB, Neptune, Timestream, S3, OpenSearch, SageMaker (volumes, Feature Store, model artifacts). TLS 1.2 or higher in transit. Audit-event payloads include PHI (the patient identifier and often patient demographics) and user PII (the workforce member's identifier and HR-linked data); both categories must be protected." The explicit acknowledgment that workforce PII is comparably sensitive to PHI is the recipe-3.9-distinctive framing that distinguishes access monitoring from other anomaly detection programs and is the operationally-correct discipline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     56[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     57[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mIAM is least-privilege with concrete examples in the Prerequisites table: "Ingest Lambdas write to the event stream and read from EHR/IdP/HRIS sources. Enrichment Lambdas read from identity stores and write enriched events downstream. Detectors read from state stores and write scores. Case builder reads scores and assembles cases. Privacy investigators read case data and write outcomes only. Data science roles can train and deploy but cannot read identifying user data without explicit elevation; training data sets are typically pseudonymized for development. No [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m*[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m permissions; every action scoped to specific resources." The "training data sets are typically pseudonymized for development" framing is the right discipline for a domain where the training data includes both workforce identifiers and patient identifiers.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     58[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     59[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mCloudTrail data events on every PHI-bearing store and on the case management indexes and on the model endpoints are required, with the explicit framing "Every score, every case generation, every adjudication, every export is logged. Log retention per organizational policy and applicable regulations (some jurisdictions and accreditation programs require multi-year retention)." This is the audit-trail discipline a hospital regulatory affairs team can defend in front of an OCR auditor or a labor counsel review.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     60[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     61[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mSynthetic data discipline is explicit and correct. The "Internal historical audit logs are the only realistic training data; no public dataset captures the breadth needed" framing is operationally accurate. The "Pseudonymization for development is essential and non-trivial: the user-patient relationship structure must be preserved while identifiers are replaced" framing names the specific challenge of pseudonymizing graph data where the relationship structure is itself the signal.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     62[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     63[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe "Privacy Office and Infosec Governance" Prerequisites row is unusually substantive and operationally accurate: "A privacy committee (typically including the Chief Privacy Officer, Chief Information Security Officer, General Counsel or HIPAA Privacy Officer designee, Compliance, HR, and clinical leadership) must own the program. Acceptable-use and monitoring policy must be in place and the workforce must be notified. Investigation procedures, appeals processes, and HR coordination protocols must be documented before deployment." This is the discipline that distinguishes mature deployments from failed pilots.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     64[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     65[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe "Workforce Notification and Acceptable Use Policy" Prerequisites row is unusually current on labor-and-legal posture: "Workforce members must be informed that monitoring exists and what it covers. The policy should align with HIPAA Security Rule audit-control requirements, applicable state privacy statutes, and any collective bargaining agreements. Counsel should review before publication." The framing acknowledges that monitoring without notification is a labor-and-legal disaster regardless of technology quality.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     66[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     67[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mStep 8's outcome capture correctly enumerates valid outcomes ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mconfirmed_violation[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdismissed_legitimate[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdismissed_inconclusive[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mescalated_to_hr[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mescalated_to_legal[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mescalated_to_law_enforcement[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) and routes each to the appropriate downstream workflow (breach-review initiation for confirmed violations, suppression-rule addition for dismissed-legitimate cases, prior-violation flag for confirmed-violation users). The "Initiate the HIPAA breach notification clock" framing for confirmed violations is the operationally-correct discipline.[K
