[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    199[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mArchitecture Expert Review[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    200[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    201[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    202[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    203[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe eight-stage pipeline (streaming ingest and normalization, identity-patient-workforce enrichment, relationship graph maintenance, per-user behavioral baselines, multi-detector bank, composite scoring with calibration, case builder with LLM narrative, privacy office case queue with SIEM integration and outcome capture) is the architecturally correct factoring for a healthcare-access-monitoring system. The decision to drive scoring from two paths (streaming per-event scoring for the rules-engine and per-event detectors, daily-cadence batch scoring for the user-graph rescoring and behavioral-baseline computations) matches the operational cadence the prose describes and the EHR-audit-log latency reality.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    204[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    205[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe layered-detector architecture (rules engine for policy-defined patterns, per-user statistical baselines for deviation patterns, graph-based detection for relationship patterns, sequence models for workflow patterns, LLM-assisted triage as a productivity layer, supervised classifier as the program matures) is the architectural discipline that distinguishes operationally-tunable systems from black-box deployments. The closing "reasonable progression" posture (rules first, then baselines, then graph, then sequence, then LLM triage, supervised classifier when labels are sufficient) is operations-engineer voice on the most consequential program-design decision.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    206[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    207[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe capacity-aware case prioritization in Step 6's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcomposite_score[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtier_from_score(... capacity = current_privacy_office_capacity())[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) acknowledges the binding constraint the prose names ("the privacy office can review tens of cases per day, not thousands"). The framing that "a system with 95% recall and 5% precision floods the queue with false positives until reviewers stop trusting it; a system with 70% recall and 25% precision is reviewable, trustable, and produces real outcomes" is operationally accurate and the architecture reflects it through capacity-bounded tier assignment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    208[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    209[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe case-grouping-and-suppression path in Step 7's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mbuild_case[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m correctly groups related events into single investigations ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfind_existing_case[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m within a case-grouping window) and applies suppression rules (recently-dismissed-pattern suppression, investigation-overlap suppression). The "the same user accessing the same patient over multiple sessions, or a session with multiple flagged accesses, becomes one case" framing is the operationally-correct discipline that distinguishes mature programs from ones that produce per-event alerts.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    210[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    211[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe outcome-capture-and-feedback path closes the feedback loop with proper label-derivation discipline. The pseudocode's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mon_investigator_action[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m correctly enumerates valid outcomes, routes confirmed-violation outcomes to breach-review and HR-referral, adds suppression rules for dismissed-legitimate outcomes, and persists the label record for retraining. This is the operationally-correct labeling path that produces the highest-quality training data given the chapter-3-acknowledged label-quality constraints.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    212[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    213[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Detector Bank's parallel-detector pattern (multiple detectors run in parallel with the composite layer combining outputs) is the architecturally correct factoring; the alternative (a single monolithic detector) would be harder to tune, harder to explain, and harder to evolve.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    214[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    215[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mSageMaker Feature Store is correctly identified as the substrate for offline/online feature consistency. SageMaker Clarify is correctly positioned for SHAP-based per-case explanations. SageMaker Model Monitor is correctly named for data drift, prediction drift, and (with labels) quality drift monitoring with the right framing for the access-monitoring program: "Critical for catching baseline drift caused by EHR upgrades, role changes, organizational restructures, and the gradual shift in workforce behavior that affects every monitoring program."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    216[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    217[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mImplementation-time tiers (4-9 months Basic with single EHR audit feed and rules engine, 12-24 months Production-ready with single EHR plus 2-3 application audit feeds and full layered detection and governance, 18-48 additional months for variations including additional EHRs, sequence models, GNN-based detection, privileged-user separate program, patient-portal access monitoring, federated cross-site monitoring, conversational AI investigator copilot) are realistic and resist optimism bias.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    218[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    219[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Variations and Extensions section covers fourteen adjacent patterns at substantive depth (vendor-tool augmentation rather than replacement, SIEM-native deployment, PAM integration, patient-portal access monitoring, identity-fabric integration, external-organization monitoring, compromised-credential detection focus, insider-threat-program integration, federated and multi-site programs, privacy-by-design for the monitoring system itself, conversational AI for case investigation, patient-facing transparency, LLM-on-policy review, cross-detection with fraud and clinical anomalies). The "vendor-tool augmentation rather than replacement" framing is the operationally-honest framing for the build-vs-buy decision. The "patient-facing transparency" framing acknowledges the emerging movement honestly.[K
