[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    400[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    401[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mBut the architecture doesn't enforce the discipline. Step 8's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mon_investigator_action[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m adds a suppression rule when the outcome is [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdismissed_legitimate[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, but the suppression-rule schema is implicit (the [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140madd_suppression_rule[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m call in the pseudocode is opaque about what fields the rule contains). A privacy office investigator filling out the dismissal-rationale form may produce a suppression rule that's too broad ("workforce_id WF-12849 -> all CARDIOLOGY_SD_UNIT_PATIENTS") or too narrow ("workforce_id WF-12849 -> patient_id PT-3382091 only"); without an explicit schema and a validation discipline, the rule library degrades over time.[K
