[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    812[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    813[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThere are zero HIGH findings. The MEDIUM findings cluster heavily on prose-vs-pseudocode asymmetry: A3 (privileged-user separate program), A4 (service-account inventory), A5 (new-user ramp-up cold-start), A6 (care-relationship suppression-rule schema-and-workflow) are all places where the prose makes a discipline claim that the canonical pseudocode walkthrough doesn't reflect. This is the same pronounced prose-vs-pseudocode-asymmetry signature as Recipe 3.8 and reflects the recipe's substantive engagement with operational realities. A7 (reference-data versioning propagation) is the same recurring pattern as Recipes 3.5, 3.6, 3.7, 3.8. A1 (idempotency) and A2 (DLQs) are the recurring chapter-wide patterns. S1 (case payload PHI-and-workforce-PII minimization) is the latest variant of the recurring chapter pattern. S2 (subgroup governance) is the eight-recipe chapter-wide pattern.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    814[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    815[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe four highest-leverage fixes are A3 (privileged-user separate program), A4 (service-account inventory), A5 (new-user ramp-up cold-start), and A6 (care-relationship suppression-rule schema-and-workflow). All four are explicitly emphasized in The Honest Take or Why-This-Isn't-Production-Ready and all four are not architecturally enforced in the pseudocode. A3 and A4 are the most-consequential teaching gaps because they affect daily operational reality (privileged users have fundamentally different patterns; service accounts appear as extreme anomalies). A5 is the most-frequent operational pain point (every role change in a 10,000-workforce health system is a cold-start event). A6 is the longest-running operational pain point (care-relationship data quality has been a known issue for over a decade and the suppression-rule library is the operational workaround).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    816[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    817[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A1 is the now-recurring trigger-idempotency pattern, surfacing for the fourteenth consecutive recipe (2.4-2.10 and 3.1-3.9). The cookbook would benefit substantially from a shared appendix that covers the patterns once. With the per-recipe-edit posture producing diminishing returns, the trigger-idempotency appendix is the highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    818[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    819[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A2 (DLQs) is operationally critical for Recipe 3.9 specifically because the system feeds privacy-office investigations, HR employment actions, and HIPAA breach-notification decisions. The DLQ-depth alarm threshold for ehr-audit-ingest, event-normalizer, enrichment, case-builder, and outcome-capture paths should be 1 (single-event sensitivity).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    820[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    821[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S1 is the now-recurring PHI-minimization-inside-the-BAA pattern with the ninth distinct surface across the cookbook. Recipe 3.9's distinctive amplification is that the case payload contains both PHI and workforce PII in equal measure, and the SIEM connector specifically has substantially broader access scope than the privacy-office UI. A cookbook-wide PHI-minimization appendix would consolidate all nine surfaces with one teaching pass.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    822[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    823[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S2 is the eight-recipe chapter-wide subgroup-governance pattern. Recipe 3.9's distinctive contribution is the workforce-equity dimension specifically (which is distinct from the patient-equity dimension addressed in Recipes 3.7 and 3.8); workforce demographic data has its own legal posture (EEOC/Title VII implementation, state employment-discrimination statutes, collective-bargaining agreements) that the architectural backstop should reflect. Treat the subgroup-governance appendix as the second-highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment alongside trigger-idempotency.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    824[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    825[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S8 (news-and-public-figure-feed integration security and policy posture) is the new surface this recipe introduces. Future recipes that integrate external content feeds (Chapter 8 NLP recipes, Chapter 11 conversational AI recipes, Chapter 13 knowledge-graphs recipes) may face the same finding shape.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    826[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    827[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A8 (self-monitoring of the monitoring system) is recipe-3.9-distinctive: only this recipe has a system that monitors a population that has access to the system itself. The architectural primitive is small (CloudTrail data events forwarded back into the audit-event pipeline) but the pedagogical implication is large (a reader could accidentally exempt the monitoring-system-access-events from the monitoring pipeline).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    828[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    829[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Honest Take section is publication-ready and should be preserved verbatim. The thirteen-paragraph structure (build the program first; the workforce member is the sensitive population; same-name and same-address rules are surprisingly high-yield; sophisticated cases are rare and often caught by accident; care-relationship data is the longest-running pain point; privileged users are a different program; LLM-assisted triage is the biggest near-term productivity improvement; biggest mistake is flooding the workforce with investigations; political reality is CISO-and-CPO joint function; training-data scarcity is a real constraint; mature programs make the false-positive rate a leading indicator; start narrower than usual; the financial story has changed; patients matter most even when invisible) is the kind of operations-engineer voice the cookbook is built on. The closing "patients matter most, even when they're invisible in the operational workflow" framing is the kind of moral-clarity framing that distinguishes the cookbook from documentation; it should not be shortened.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    830[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    831[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe opening cardiology-step-down-nurse vignette is the densest healthcare-access-monitoring framing in any cookbook recipe and should not be shortened. The 11:47 p.m. on a Tuesday opening, the nurse who shares a last name with the patient and lives on the same street, the ninety seconds in the chart, the six audit events out of forty million, the legitimate user account at her usual workstation, the broad EHR access configured for clinical workflow flexibility, the absence of any flag firing, the three-week-later complaint from the patient about his cousin asking about a medication he hadn't told her about, the privacy-office investigation, the termination, the OCR breach notification, the civil suit, the local newspaper, and the CIO call from the CEO that begins with "explain to me how this happened" are publication-ready voice and operationally accurate.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    832[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    833[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe "Healthcare has a specific structural problem that makes this hard" reframe is the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution and is the design distinction most published treatments of UEBA blur. The framing that broad clinical access is not a bug but a feature should be preserved verbatim.[K
